55.1	Clayton_M._Christensen	Clayton M. Christensen	Clayton M. Christensen (born April 6, 1952) is the Robert and Jane Cizik Professor of Business Administration at the Harvard Business School, with a joint appointment in the Technology &amp; Operations Management and General Management faculty groups. He is best known for his study of innovation in commercial enterprises. His first book, The Innovator's Dilemma, articulated his theory of disruptive innovation.	
